HEADWORD: Sea raven
<hw>Sea" ra"ven</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>An American cottoid fish (<spn>Hemitripterus Americanus</spn>)
allied to the sculpins, found on the northern Atlantic coasts.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The cormorant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

